# Arduino Pin Configuration â€“ HomeGuard System

This document describes the pin connections between the Arduino Nano and various sensors used in the HomeGuard multi-sensor safety system.

## Digital Input Pins

| Arduino Pin | Connected Component            | Description                         |
|------------|--------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| D2         | PIR Motion Sensor              | Detects abnormal motion             |
| D3         | Magnetic Gate Sensor           | Detects main gate open/close         |
| D4         | Magnetic Door Sensor           | Detects main door open/close         |
| D5         | Water Level Sensor             | Detects high water level             |
| D6         | Rain Sensor                    | Detects rain condition               |
| D7         | High Voltage Detection Module  | Detects abnormal AC voltage          |
| D8         | LDR (Light Sensor)             | Detects ambient light changes        |

## I2C Interface

| Arduino Pin | Component | Description           |
|------------|-----------|-----------------------|
| A4         | SDA       | LCD data line         |
| A5         | SCL       | LCD clock line        |

## Output Components

- 16x2 LCD with I2C module for alert display
- LEDs for individual sensor indication
- Relay modules for automatic safety control

## Notes
- All digital pins are configured as INPUT in the program.
- Proper pull-up or pull-down resistors are used where required.
- Power supply connections are isolated for safety.


